comment: The quotient of a topological group by a closed normal subgroup is a Hausdorff topological group. In particular, the quotient by the closure of the identity is a Hausdorff topological group, isomorphic to both the Kolmogorov quotient and the Hausdorff quotient operations on topological spaces (because T0 and Hausdorff coincide for topological groups). (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 22-Sep-2015.)
